Present location: INSTITUT DE PAPYROLOGIE ET D'ÉGYPTOLOGIE, UNIVERSITÉ DE LILLE III [02/049] LILLE
Name: Mummy breast cover
Description: Mummy breast cover with, at the top, a kneeling goddess (Nut) with out-stretched wings, coiffed by the solar disc and holding the feather of Maat in each hand. She is flanked by two udjat-eyes. At the bottom, the reclining mummy, alone, flanked by ''palace facade'' motifs. Brick-red background.
